Welcome to the Sitan Mansion.

39
00:03:40,940 --> 00:03:42,820
This is
the Shanghai Symphony Orchestra's

40
00:03:42,820 --> 00:03:44,690
Four Seasons Concert.

41
00:03:44,780 --> 00:03:46,660
(Sitan Mansion)

42
00:03:47,010 --> 00:03:48,380
Today we have invited

43
00:03:48,380 --> 00:03:51,610
two comedians from Banghe Comedy Club.

44
00:03:51,610 --> 00:03:55,170
Now, please enjoy the performance
by Wu Xiuya.

45
00:04:00,940 --> 00:04:02,820
Hello, everyone, my name is Wu Xiuya.

46
00:04:08,660 --> 00:04:10,780
I really enjoy earning money at work,

47
00:04:11,100 --> 00:04:13,100
but I really don't like working
at the office.

48
00:04:13,380 --> 00:04:14,420
At the age of mid-twenties,

49
00:04:14,420 --> 00:04:16,660
we are considered the youngest
in the company.

50
00:04:16,660 --> 00:04:19,810
We're the so-called
third-generation employees, the grandsons.

51
00:04:22,100 --> 00:04:23,980
And yet, we are very unhappy.

52
00:04:23,980 --> 00:04:26,250
So we are the unworthy descendants
of the company.

53
00:04:39,540 --> 00:04:40,930
Until one day,

54
00:04:40,930 --> 00:04:42,540
there was a Financial Summit.

55
00:04:42,660 --> 00:04:44,930
The Chairman asked me to attend,
not my leader,

56
00:04:45,660 --> 00:04:47,250
which made her very unhappy.

57
00:04:47,580 --> 00:04:48,730
I just realized

58
00:04:48,730 --> 00:04:51,170
there are people
who really like this kind of activity.

59
00:04:51,610 --> 00:04:54,610
I call this kind of activity
"workplace Frisbee".

60
00:04:55,050 --> 00:04:56,900
It's completely useless.

61
00:04:56,900 --> 00:04:58,610
As soon as the boss throws it out,

62
00:04:58,610 --> 00:05:00,610
the lapdogs scramble to grab it,

63
00:05:00,900 --> 00:05:04,020
thinking, "As long as I perform well,

64
00:05:04,020 --> 00:05:05,780
the master will value me."

65
00:05:09,340 --> 00:05:11,490
So how did my leader
retaliate against me later?

66
00:05:11,780 --> 00:05:14,340
It was by editing me out
of the group photo.

67
00:05:14,460 --> 00:05:16,770
The workplace bullying
I experienced was actually assaulted

68
00:05:16,770 --> 00:05:19,050
by my leader with Photoshop.

69
00:05:19,050 --> 00:05:20,900
She gave me a cut from behind.

70
00:05:22,610 --> 00:05:23,780
And do you know

71
00:05:23,780 --> 00:05:26,050
why did she edit me out?

72
00:05:26,340 --> 00:05:28,730
Because my ex-boyfriend and I
were in it.

73
00:05:29,050 --> 00:05:31,020
If this group photo was sent out,

74
00:05:31,020 --> 00:05:32,340
all the colleagues

75
00:05:32,340 --> 00:05:34,340
would focus on the gossip

76
00:05:34,340 --> 00:05:37,050
about my breakup with my ex-boyfriend

77
00:05:37,610 --> 00:05:39,050
and neglect the Chairman.

78
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:42,580
Thank you, everyone.

79
00:05:42,580 --> 00:05:45,290
I am the unworthy descendant
of the company, Wu Xiuya.

80
00:06:00,700 --> 00:06:03,850
Let's thank Wu Xiuya
for the wonderful performance.

81
00:06:03,930 --> 00:06:06,340
Let's welcome the next performer,

82
00:06:06,700 --> 00:06:08,460
Liang Dong.

83
00:06:12,410 --> 00:06:13,450
What's wrong? It's not over yet.

84
00:06:13,450 --> 00:06:15,330
- Xiaolan, it's urgent.
- Hello everyone, I'm Liang Dong.

85
00:06:15,330 --> 00:06:16,490
Slow down. Careful.

86
00:06:19,170 --> 00:06:21,490
Today, I am especially honored…

87
00:06:57,940 --> 00:07:03,780
(Sitan Mansion)

88
00:07:03,780 --> 00:07:08,140
=Episode 13=

89
00:07:13,780 --> 00:07:15,370
(The Chairman's expression)

90
00:07:15,730 --> 00:07:17,900
(was as stern as usual.)

91
00:07:19,100 --> 00:07:21,700
(Zheng Hao couldn't endure
the prolonged silence.)

92
00:07:22,100 --> 00:07:23,410
(He tried to speak several times,)

93
00:07:23,700 --> 00:07:26,410
(but didn't know what
to say to break it.)

94
00:07:26,780 --> 00:07:28,700
(He could only give up in the end.)

95
00:07:28,990 --> 00:07:29,830
Zheng,

96
00:07:31,940 --> 00:07:34,410
has the Marketing Department reached
an agreement with Wharton?

97
00:07:34,410 --> 00:07:37,290
(Zheng Hao thought the Chairman
wanted to discuss Xiuya's matter,)

98
00:07:37,700 --> 00:07:39,980
(yet he started talking about work.)
They

99
00:07:39,980 --> 00:07:41,700
are currently at a stalemate.

100
00:07:42,410 --> 00:07:44,680
The hardest part of collaborating
with foreign enterprises

101
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:45,980
is establishing mutual trust.

102
00:07:46,980 --> 00:07:47,900
That's right.

103
00:07:48,220 --> 00:07:49,340
When collaborating with them,

104
00:07:49,340 --> 00:07:51,850
not only do we need to reach
consensus on the operational level,

105
00:07:51,850 --> 00:07:54,900
but also have common topics
in cultural understanding.

106
00:07:55,290 --> 00:07:56,730
Otherwise, it's difficult to sustain.

107
00:07:57,780 --> 00:07:59,900
(In the meanwhile,
Xiuya didn't know how to face)

108
00:07:59,900 --> 00:08:01,340
(what happened today.)

109
00:08:01,700 --> 00:08:03,900
(She just wanted to hide
and be an ostrich.)

110
00:08:06,540 --> 00:08:07,540
I'm doomed.

111
00:08:07,540 --> 00:08:08,980
They all left early.

112
00:08:08,980 --> 00:08:10,780
The Chairman must be angry.

113
00:08:10,900 --> 00:08:12,700
Maybe they really
had something to do.

114
00:08:12,980 --> 00:08:13,980
How's that possible?

115
00:08:13,980 --> 00:08:16,340
It's like disturbing the lion
in his den.

116
00:08:16,340 --> 00:08:17,410
I'm dead.

117
00:08:19,780 --> 00:08:21,220
Stay calm.

118
00:08:23,340 --> 00:08:24,180
Yes.

119
00:08:24,980 --> 00:08:25,850
Stay calm.

120
00:08:26,540 --> 00:08:27,900
What is stand-up comedy?

121
00:08:28,220 --> 00:08:30,170
Stand-up comedy is the art of roasting.

122
00:08:30,170 --> 00:08:31,020
And what is art?

123
00:08:31,030 --> 00:08:32,530
Art is above life.

124
00:08:32,530 --> 00:08:34,530
It requires refinement and processing.

125
00:08:34,790 --> 00:08:36,220
The Chairman is such
an open-minded person.

126
00:08:36,220 --> 00:08:37,700
He can definitely understand.

127
00:08:38,890 --> 00:08:39,890
I'm sure he can.

128
00:08:41,300 --> 00:08:42,340
No, no.

129
00:08:42,420 --> 00:08:44,100
He won't understand.

130
00:08:45,220 --> 00:08:46,700
He won't understand at all.

131
00:08:46,700 --> 00:08:47,980
The Chairman doesn't even know

132
00:08:47,980 --> 00:08:49,340
what stand-up comedy is.

133
00:08:49,340 --> 00:08:51,730
He is a stern middle-aged man.

134
00:08:51,890 --> 00:08:53,360
In his heart, the company comes first,

135
00:08:53,360 --> 00:08:54,910
and the company's reputation
is above all else.

136
00:08:54,910 --> 00:08:56,340
No boss can accept

137
00:08:56,340 --> 00:08:58,700
being joked about in public.

138
00:08:59,770 --> 00:09:01,220
I need to attend a meeting tomorrow

139
00:09:01,220 --> 00:09:02,890
where the Chairman
will also be present.

140
00:09:02,890 --> 00:09:04,420
How am I supposed to face him?

141
00:09:05,700 --> 00:09:08,530
I think your people-pleasing
personality is acting up again.

142
00:09:08,530 --> 00:09:09,850
Just face it normally.

143
00:09:09,850 --> 00:09:11,340
Even if he's upset,

144
00:09:11,340 --> 00:09:12,340
what could happen?

145
00:09:12,530 --> 00:09:14,300
I could lose my job.

146
00:09:14,420 --> 00:09:15,980
Then there's nothing to be afraid of.

147
00:09:15,980 --> 00:09:17,700
When you marry Xu Yunfeng,

148
00:09:17,850 --> 00:09:20,300
you'll be worth more
than your company.

149
00:09:20,300 --> 00:09:22,420
I'm more curious
about Zheng Hao's reaction.

150
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:26,700
It was also the first time
he saw me do stand-up comedy.

151
00:09:28,770 --> 00:09:31,100
Many of my jokes
are actually about him.

152
00:09:32,420 --> 00:09:33,700
He must think

153
00:09:33,770 --> 00:09:35,100
I'm the kind of petty, mean woman

154
00:09:35,100 --> 00:09:37,100
who deliberately talks bad about him

155
00:09:37,100 --> 00:09:38,850
in public after a breakup.

156
00:09:40,220 --> 00:09:41,700
Then he is mistaken.

157
00:09:41,760 --> 00:09:43,800
You didn't just start talking bad
about him after the breakup.

158
00:09:43,800 --> 00:09:45,420
It already started before.

159
00:09:49,530 --> 00:09:50,730
Then how can I ask him

160
00:09:50,730 --> 00:09:52,220
if the Chairman is angry?

161
00:09:54,220 --> 00:09:55,850
He might yell at you.

162
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:56,890
But if I don't ask him,

163
00:09:56,890 --> 00:09:59,300
I won't know if the Chairman is upset.

164
00:10:01,340 --> 00:10:02,700
Actually, for every question,

165
00:10:02,700 --> 00:10:04,890
you already have an answer.

166
00:10:05,890 --> 00:10:06,770
But I need

167
00:10:06,770 --> 00:10:08,700
to talk out loud to clear my thoughts.

168
00:10:08,700 --> 00:10:10,300
Understood. Let me.

169
00:10:10,980 --> 00:10:11,890
I'll ask for you.

170
00:10:13,730 --> 00:10:15,420
Hey, Siri.

171
00:10:15,980 --> 00:10:17,980
How can I help you?

172
00:10:17,980 --> 00:10:20,980
Xiuya asks if the Chairman
is upset with her.

173
00:10:21,340 --> 00:10:22,730
Stop it.

174
00:10:23,010 --> 00:10:24,250
I didn't find "the Chairman"

175
00:10:24,250 --> 00:10:25,300
in your contacts.

176
00:10:25,300 --> 00:10:26,770
Shall I ask Zheng Hao?

177
00:10:27,420 --> 00:10:28,260
Okay.

178
00:10:32,340 --> 00:10:33,780
(The other party is typing…)

179
00:10:33,780 --> 00:10:35,890
He must be typing something to scold me.

180
00:10:40,780 --> 00:10:41,980
(Wu Xiuya: Please call back quickly.)

181
00:10:41,980 --> 00:10:43,820
(Find a chance to apologize
to the Chairman in private!)

182
00:10:55,770 --> 00:10:57,610
Cheer up, will you?

183
00:10:57,610 --> 00:10:59,770
You've been sulking all night.

184
00:11:06,040 --> 00:11:06,890
Let's play a game.

185
00:11:07,300 --> 00:11:08,140
Not in the mood.

186
00:11:08,300 --> 00:11:09,140
Come on.

187
00:11:09,190 --> 00:11:10,160
Don't wanna play.

188
00:11:10,180 --> 00:11:11,020
Why not?

189
00:11:11,250 --> 00:11:12,890
I'm not in the mood to play games.

190
00:11:12,890 --> 00:11:14,150
Between us, who calls who dad?

191
00:11:14,160 --> 00:11:15,250
Between us, you call me dad.

192
00:11:15,250 --> 00:11:16,410
Between us, who calls who son?

193
00:11:16,410 --> 00:11:17,490
Between us, I call you son.

194
00:11:17,490 --> 00:11:18,700
Between us, who's whose dad?

195
00:11:18,700 --> 00:11:19,770
Between us, you are my…

196
00:11:21,420 --> 00:11:22,530
I lost.

197
00:11:24,120 --> 00:11:25,150
Again, come on.

198
00:11:26,530 --> 00:11:27,370
I'm done.

199
00:11:29,530 --> 00:11:32,300
She has to apologize for what she said.

200
00:11:32,530 --> 00:11:33,700
A normal person

201
00:11:33,700 --> 00:11:35,700
would definitely find
an opportunity to apologize.

202
00:11:36,010 --> 00:11:37,010
Others would,

203
00:11:38,010 --> 00:11:38,890
but she wouldn't.

204
00:11:39,160 --> 00:11:40,300
She's not a normal person?

205
00:11:48,100 --> 00:11:50,020
(Wu Xiuya, I still think you should…)

206
00:11:55,530 --> 00:11:56,370
Forget it.

207
00:11:57,700 --> 00:11:58,890
Who am I to her anyway?

208
00:11:59,300 --> 00:12:00,770
You are her ex-boyfriend.

209
00:12:03,010 --> 00:12:05,700
Just treat this as gossip.

210
00:12:06,700 --> 00:12:08,890
Don't always think
about saving other people.

211
00:12:11,250 --> 00:12:13,300
The thing is, I just don't understand

212
00:12:14,700 --> 00:12:17,530
why Wu Xiuya suddenly
became like this.

213
00:12:18,250 --> 00:12:19,300
But you're right.

214
00:12:21,010 --> 00:12:23,010
How she behaves
is not my business anymore.

215
00:12:23,250 --> 00:12:24,700
Now that you said that,

216
00:12:24,890 --> 00:12:26,890
it's not entirely unrelated, actually.

217
00:12:27,250 --> 00:12:29,300
Didn't she just joke
about you on stage?

218
00:12:30,530 --> 00:12:31,700
Let me ask you,

219
00:12:31,890 --> 00:12:34,890
how does it feel to be joked about?

220
00:12:40,050 --> 00:12:40,930
If I tell you

221
00:12:42,890 --> 00:12:46,370
it felt good being mocked

222
00:12:47,010 --> 00:12:48,300
by my ex-girlfriend,

223
00:12:49,250 --> 00:12:50,090
will you believe me?

224
00:12:52,010 --> 00:12:52,890
I'm impressed.

225
00:12:55,890 --> 00:12:58,250
(Zheng Hao didn't know
how to explain his mixed feelings.)

226
00:12:58,530 --> 00:13:00,300
(Hearing Xiuya mock him,)

227
00:13:00,530 --> 00:13:01,890
(he surely felt angry.)

228
00:13:06,530 --> 00:13:08,370
I've never seen Xiuya like that.

229
00:13:19,500 --> 00:13:21,300
(Zheng Hao)

230
00:13:21,530 --> 00:13:23,770
Will he tell me or not?

231
00:13:49,250 --> 00:13:50,890
(Thinking about meeting
the Chairman,)

232
00:13:51,370 --> 00:13:53,250
(Xiuya got extremely nervous.)

233
00:13:53,770 --> 00:13:56,010
(The building in front of her
was full of unknowns.)

234
00:13:56,420 --> 00:13:57,530
(She dared not imagine)

235
00:13:57,530 --> 00:13:59,490
(what would happen next.)

236
00:14:02,610 --> 00:14:04,250
He's literally looking for death.

237
00:14:04,250 --> 00:14:06,700
He put it on paper
when offering advice to his boss,

238
00:14:06,740 --> 00:14:08,250
with a chance to get back at him later.

239
00:14:08,370 --> 00:14:09,890
No boss would appreciate opinions.

240
00:14:10,010 --> 00:14:11,110
They say they want your opinions,

241
00:14:11,180 --> 00:14:13,260
but in fact, it's a trap.

242
00:14:13,260 --> 00:14:15,530
He only picked the times
when the Chairman was not around.

243
00:14:15,530 --> 00:14:17,420
And then he got angry himself.

244
00:14:18,300 --> 00:14:19,420
So you wanted

245
00:14:19,420 --> 00:14:21,250
to travel with your boyfriend

246
00:14:21,250 --> 00:14:22,530
while the Chairman was in the Maldives?

247
00:14:22,610 --> 00:14:23,490
But you failed?

248
00:14:23,490 --> 00:14:25,700
Forget it. Employees like us

249
00:14:25,700 --> 00:14:27,370
can rarely get an opportunity like this.

250
00:14:29,700 --> 00:14:31,890
This one can't make
spreadsheets either.

251
00:14:32,010 --> 00:14:33,300
He's even worse than me.

252
00:14:34,700 --> 00:14:36,890
So how did the Chairman
respond to it?

253
00:14:36,910 --> 00:14:38,070
What happened to the Chairman?

254
00:14:39,420 --> 00:14:40,700
You also like this show?

255
00:14:41,370 --> 00:14:42,420
Wanna join us?

256
00:14:45,770 --> 00:14:47,700
No. You guys go ahead and watch.

257
00:15:01,010 --> 00:15:01,890
Are you alright?

258
00:15:01,890 --> 00:15:03,770
You've been acting weird
since this morning.

259
00:15:04,530 --> 00:15:05,370
I'm fine.

260
00:15:08,130 --> 00:15:09,130
Just a little cold.

261
00:15:13,130 --> 00:15:15,010
The Chairman can't be here today.

262
00:15:15,130 --> 00:15:17,180
He asked me to preside
over this meeting.

263
00:15:17,300 --> 00:15:19,060
Next, I will convey some

264
00:15:19,060 --> 00:15:20,760
optimization instructions
from the Chairman

265
00:15:20,760 --> 00:15:21,770
to the internal employees.

266
00:15:22,150 --> 00:15:23,010
(When Xiuya found out)

267
00:15:23,010 --> 00:15:25,490
(that the Chairman would not
attend the meeting,)

268
00:15:25,760 --> 00:15:27,420
(the tension she had been
feeling all day)

269
00:15:27,420 --> 00:15:28,890
(finally eased.)

270
00:15:29,300 --> 00:15:31,370
(But she also knew she couldn't)

271
00:15:31,700 --> 00:15:33,300
(Zheng Hao)
(keep avoiding like this.)

272
00:15:45,530 --> 00:15:47,300
Hello? I have something to ask you.

273
00:15:48,180 --> 00:15:49,530
I can't talk right now.

274
00:15:50,700 --> 00:15:52,300
I want to ask you if the Chairman…

275
00:15:52,420 --> 00:15:54,490
We are in a meeting together.
Talk to you later.

276
00:16:04,530 --> 00:16:07,250
Xiuya, you need to stay strong.

277
00:16:07,370 --> 00:16:09,700
You cannot fall even if I do.

278
00:16:13,890 --> 00:16:16,250
What's the punishment gonna be?

279
00:16:17,300 --> 00:16:19,010
Just give me a direct answer.

280
00:16:23,740 --> 00:16:24,580
(Zheng Hao)

281
00:16:24,580 --> 00:16:25,890
Zheng Hao is calling me.

282
00:16:27,540 --> 00:16:28,380
Hello?

283
00:16:28,770 --> 00:16:30,010
The meeting is over.

284
00:16:30,180 --> 00:16:32,010
Where are you?
Let's meet so we can talk.

285
00:16:32,140 --> 00:16:33,300
I'll send you my location.

286
00:16:34,490 --> 00:16:35,360
Let's go to Banghe.

287
00:16:35,360 --> 00:16:36,820
My international express
package is arrived.

288
00:16:36,820 --> 00:16:37,890
I'll go back to receive it.

289
00:16:38,180 --> 00:16:39,250
Alright, hurry up.

290
00:16:39,250 --> 00:16:40,180
Wait for me over there.

291
00:16:40,190 --> 00:16:41,420
- Okay.
- I'll see you soon.

292
00:16:41,420 --> 00:16:42,260
Alright.

293
00:16:47,420 --> 00:16:48,260
Thank you.

294
00:16:53,010 --> 00:16:53,850
Hello?

295
00:16:54,060 --> 00:16:54,900
Xiaolan.

296
00:16:55,530 --> 00:16:56,370
Dad.

297
00:16:56,490 --> 00:16:57,370
Let me ask you,

298
00:16:57,480 --> 00:16:59,770
has your credit card
been fraudulently charged?

299
00:17:00,250 --> 00:17:01,700
Why is the bill I received

300
00:17:02,200 --> 00:17:03,420
from Shanghai?

301
00:17:05,250 --> 00:17:07,420
Maybe the credit card company
made a mistake.

302
00:17:07,420 --> 00:17:09,700
It seems it really was
fraudulently charged.

303
00:17:10,380 --> 00:17:11,900
Online shopping is not safe.

304
00:17:11,900 --> 00:17:13,290
It happens a lot nowadays.

305
00:17:13,700 --> 00:17:16,700
No worries, I will contact the bank

306
00:17:16,900 --> 00:17:18,900
and have your credit card cancelled.

307
00:17:18,910 --> 00:17:20,010
And then I'll get you a new card.

308
00:17:20,010 --> 00:17:22,010
- Don't!
- Please take a look at this.

309
00:17:24,010 --> 00:17:24,900
Xiaolan,

310
00:17:25,290 --> 00:17:27,700
why did I just hear a Chinese man?

311
00:17:29,700 --> 00:17:32,700
Well, there are Chinese in the U.S.

312
00:17:32,900 --> 00:17:34,490
Ms. Chen, I'm on my way right now.

313
00:17:35,530 --> 00:17:37,900
Xiaolan, where are you?

314
00:17:42,770 --> 00:17:44,010
Shanghai.

315
00:17:45,680 --> 00:17:46,530
You snuck back home

316
00:17:46,530 --> 00:17:48,010
without telling us?

317
00:17:48,250 --> 00:17:49,620
What about your school?

318
00:17:49,620 --> 00:17:51,900
I know I shouldn't have
kept it from you,

319
00:17:52,010 --> 00:17:54,700
but I really don't want
to go back to that school.

320
00:17:54,700 --> 00:17:56,900
Buy a ticket and go back
to the U.S. immediately.

321
00:17:58,380 --> 00:17:59,290
I'm not going back.

322
00:17:59,420 --> 00:18:01,490
Then what are you doing in Shanghai?

323
00:18:02,250 --> 00:18:03,770
Dad, don't worry about me, okay?

324
00:18:03,770 --> 00:18:05,140
When the time is right,

325
00:18:05,140 --> 00:18:06,380
I will tell you.

326
00:18:06,530 --> 00:18:08,180
Alright, Zhao Xiaolan,

327
00:18:08,420 --> 00:18:11,530
listen up, I won't force you,

328
00:18:11,700 --> 00:18:13,010
but I'm going to cancel

329
00:18:13,180 --> 00:18:14,530
your credit card right now.

330
00:18:14,620 --> 00:18:15,700
I mean it.

331
00:18:16,010 --> 00:18:16,850
Dad…

332
00:18:18,140 --> 00:18:18,980
He hung up.

333
00:18:20,770 --> 00:18:22,420
Is he really going to cancel my card?

334
00:18:23,180 --> 00:18:27,700
(Banghe)

335
00:18:42,900 --> 00:18:48,340
(Banghe)

336
00:18:48,420 --> 00:18:49,700
Thank you everyone, I am Shi Ye.

337
00:19:08,900 --> 00:19:10,380
Have we met somewhere before?

338
00:19:13,810 --> 00:19:14,650
We've fought before.

339
00:19:19,660 --> 00:19:20,780
You don't remember me at all,

340
00:19:20,780 --> 00:19:21,610
do you?

341
00:19:22,700 --> 00:19:23,540
Well,

342
00:19:23,940 --> 00:19:25,900
I've got a big mouth

343
00:19:26,570 --> 00:19:28,420
and I always get beaten. Sorry.

344
00:19:33,330 --> 00:19:34,170
Forget it.

345
00:19:34,460 --> 00:19:35,460
Is Wu Xiuya here?

346
00:19:39,810 --> 00:19:41,090
I remember who you are now.

347
00:19:41,790 --> 00:19:42,860
I'm warning you.

348
00:19:43,420 --> 00:19:45,570
Don't treat Xiuya
with a playful attitude.

349
00:19:45,900 --> 00:19:47,220
Don't let your momentary whim

350
00:19:47,220 --> 00:19:49,090
ruin the life she has
worked hard to achieve.

351
00:19:49,810 --> 00:19:51,180
If something goes wrong,

352
00:19:51,700 --> 00:19:53,220
she has to bear it herself.

353
00:19:53,620 --> 00:19:54,460
(Shi Ye realized)

354
00:19:54,460 --> 00:19:56,900
(Zheng Hao misunderstood
his relationship with Xiuya.)

355
00:19:57,180 --> 00:19:59,700
(But with his personality,
he wouldn't explain,)

356
00:20:00,050 --> 00:20:01,700
(nor would he want to explain.)

357
00:20:02,180 --> 00:20:03,090
I feel

358
00:20:03,900 --> 00:20:04,860
that Xiuya

359
00:20:05,180 --> 00:20:07,700
is a natural stand-up comedian,

360
00:20:08,050 --> 00:20:10,090
and she loves stand-up comedy.

361
00:20:10,420 --> 00:20:12,330
In fact, the life you mentioned,

362
00:20:12,700 --> 00:20:14,220
which she has worked hard to achieve,

363
00:20:15,180 --> 00:20:16,570
is not something she wants.

364
00:20:24,090 --> 00:20:24,930
Zheng Hao,

365
00:20:25,700 --> 00:20:26,900
you arrived so early.

366
00:20:30,360 --> 00:20:31,370
I came early for the show.

367
00:20:36,560 --> 00:20:38,140
The Chairman's opinion
is not important.

368
00:20:38,220 --> 00:20:39,900
What matters is your attitude.

369
00:20:40,360 --> 00:20:42,260
I hope you can go
and apologize to the Chairman.

370
00:20:43,050 --> 00:20:44,140
Contradictory.

371
00:20:46,330 --> 00:20:47,700
I'm talking to Xiuya.

372
00:20:47,700 --> 00:20:49,220
And how am I being contradictory?

373
00:20:49,390 --> 00:20:51,090
Is the Chairman's opinion
important or not?

374
00:20:51,360 --> 00:20:53,210
If not important, why does she
have to apologize to him?

375
00:20:53,660 --> 00:20:55,240
Besides, Xiuya didn't
do anything wrong.

376
00:20:56,330 --> 00:20:57,900
It's just an expression.

377
00:20:58,220 --> 00:21:01,180
Life isn't as simple as black and white.

378
00:21:01,560 --> 00:21:02,450
We don't just apologize

379
00:21:02,450 --> 00:21:04,180
when we make mistakes.

380
00:21:04,700 --> 00:21:06,090
At work, apologizing

381
00:21:06,090 --> 00:21:07,860
is merely an expression of attitude.

382
00:21:07,900 --> 00:21:09,330
You can even consider it

383
00:21:10,090 --> 00:21:12,180
a means of communication.

384
00:21:12,360 --> 00:21:14,850
The purpose is to ensure the Chairman
does not have a prejudice against you.

385
00:21:15,140 --> 00:21:17,220
The Chairman is
the biggest leader of our group.

386
00:21:17,220 --> 00:21:18,700
You joked about him on stage

387
00:21:18,700 --> 00:21:20,180
in front of so many people.

388
00:21:20,180 --> 00:21:21,380
You disrespected him,

389
00:21:21,380 --> 00:21:22,900
and that was wrong.

390
00:21:22,900 --> 00:21:24,090
Stand-up comedy is an art form

391
00:21:24,700 --> 00:21:26,460
based on offensive material.

392
00:21:27,860 --> 00:21:29,130
You are quite artistic right now.

393
00:21:29,130 --> 00:21:30,330
Why don't you come and join us?

394
00:21:36,420 --> 00:21:37,260
Thank you.

395
00:21:40,570 --> 00:21:41,410
Let's talk.

396
00:21:42,900 --> 00:21:46,460
I think I can explain to the Chairman

397
00:21:46,760 --> 00:21:48,770
that stand-up comedy is
just a form of performance.

398
00:21:48,810 --> 00:21:50,160
It takes some elements from life

399
00:21:50,160 --> 00:21:51,190
and pushes them to the extreme.

400
00:21:51,200 --> 00:21:52,440
He shouldn't take it personally.

401
00:21:53,090 --> 00:21:54,420
Don't explain.

402
00:21:54,420 --> 00:21:56,700
At work, the last thing
you wanna do is to explain.

403
00:21:56,700 --> 00:21:57,760
What to explain anyway?

404
00:21:57,760 --> 00:21:59,610
The Chairman misunderstood.
You were not wrong.

405
00:21:59,610 --> 00:22:01,050
It's not your problem,
it's all his.

406
00:22:01,050 --> 00:22:01,890
Really?

407
00:22:02,380 --> 00:22:04,050
I think he made a good point here.

408
00:22:04,220 --> 00:22:06,310
If I had to go off stage
to explain my performance

409
00:22:06,310 --> 00:22:07,940
to the audience
every time I finished it,

410
00:22:07,940 --> 00:22:09,140
I'd go crazy.

411
00:22:10,700 --> 00:22:12,860
When everyone is there
flattering the Chairman,

412
00:22:12,860 --> 00:22:13,900
making him laugh,

413
00:22:13,900 --> 00:22:15,420
that's called the year-end party.

414
00:22:15,700 --> 00:22:17,700
But you are doing
stand-up comedy on stage.

415
00:22:18,090 --> 00:22:20,900
When you stand on stage, you are
up there as a stand-up comedian,

416
00:22:20,900 --> 00:22:22,900
not a company employee.

417
00:22:23,900 --> 00:22:25,420
I agree with Shi Ye.

418
00:22:25,620 --> 00:22:27,700
Stand-up comedy is just an art form.

419
00:22:28,420 --> 00:22:30,620
Xiuya didn't joke about the leaders

420
00:22:30,620 --> 00:22:31,700
at a company meeting.

421
00:22:31,900 --> 00:22:33,700
You came to the show uninvited.

422
00:22:33,900 --> 00:22:35,700
Besides, he's the Chairman.

423
00:22:35,900 --> 00:22:37,140
As a Chairman, he's supposed

424
00:22:37,140 --> 00:22:38,700
to be broad-minded, right?

425
00:22:38,700 --> 00:22:40,700
He wouldn't punish an employee

426
00:22:40,760 --> 00:22:42,110
just because of a few jokes, right?

427
00:22:42,420 --> 00:22:43,380
No leader

428
00:22:43,380 --> 00:22:45,330
can accept this kind of challenge.

429
00:22:45,420 --> 00:22:47,050
Sure, the Chairman is a decent person.

430
00:22:47,050 --> 00:22:48,940
He won't do anything
to you in a public setting,

431
00:22:48,940 --> 00:22:51,180
nor will he punish you
for such a trivial matter.

432
00:22:51,360 --> 00:22:52,900
However, as an employee,

433
00:22:52,900 --> 00:22:55,140
if you don't have any
positive remedial measures,

434
00:22:55,140 --> 00:22:56,900
you'll become invisible
to the Chairman.

435
00:22:57,420 --> 00:22:59,180
Xiuya, for an employee of your level,

436
00:22:59,180 --> 00:23:00,860
he doesn't even need to do anything

437
00:23:00,960 --> 00:23:03,340
for you to disappear in time.

438
00:23:03,900 --> 00:23:06,160
But Xiuya was promoted
by the Chairman

439
00:23:06,160 --> 00:23:07,490
because she dared
to challenge the rules

440
00:23:07,490 --> 00:23:08,500
and his leadership, right?

441
00:23:08,940 --> 00:23:10,860
She challenged her direct supervisor,

442
00:23:10,860 --> 00:23:12,420
not the Chairman himself.

443
00:23:13,180 --> 00:23:15,900
Xiuya, all the efforts
you made at work

444
00:23:15,900 --> 00:23:17,420
will be denied right away.

445
00:23:17,420 --> 00:23:18,440
Are you willing to accept that?

446
00:23:19,330 --> 00:23:20,810
If all of Xiuya's work

447
00:23:20,810 --> 00:23:22,600
and efforts are denied

448
00:23:22,600 --> 00:23:24,140
not because she made
a mistake at work,

449
00:23:24,140 --> 00:23:25,460
but because of something she said,

450
00:23:25,570 --> 00:23:26,530
who would accept

451
00:23:26,530 --> 00:23:27,570
a working environment like that?

452
00:23:28,570 --> 00:23:30,570
Xiuya has the right
to choose her own happiness.

453
00:23:30,900 --> 00:23:32,380
If there's only one option,

454
00:23:32,460 --> 00:23:33,700
how is she supposed to choose?

455
00:23:34,180 --> 00:23:35,570
If a person loses his subjectivity,

456
00:23:35,660 --> 00:23:37,050
what is there
to discuss about acceptance?

457
00:23:37,050 --> 00:23:39,180
Can you stop mentioning
Xiuya for a moment?

458
00:23:39,220 --> 00:23:40,860
Alright, you can be idealistic.

459
00:23:40,900 --> 00:23:42,180
You can all be idealistic.

460
00:23:42,180 --> 00:23:43,010
But

461
00:23:43,010 --> 00:23:45,590
what about the reality you have to face
after a moment of passion?

462
00:23:45,940 --> 00:23:46,810
If you lose this job,

463
00:23:46,810 --> 00:23:48,160
you still have to find another one.

464
00:23:48,380 --> 00:23:50,230
This is a problem you always
have to deal with.

465
00:23:50,700 --> 00:23:52,100
As long as you still have sociality,

466
00:23:52,100 --> 00:23:54,900
you will inevitably have to face this.

467
00:24:00,900 --> 00:24:02,420
- Let me think about it.
- You don't have to.

468
00:24:02,420 --> 00:24:03,460
You must apologize,

469
00:24:03,810 --> 00:24:05,180
and you can't do it in a blunt way

470
00:24:05,180 --> 00:24:07,220
by apologizing to the Chairman
in front of others.

471
00:24:07,220 --> 00:24:08,700
We are the only ones who know.

472
00:24:09,090 --> 00:24:10,000
If others find out,

473
00:24:10,000 --> 00:24:11,700
the Chairman will be
even more embarrassed.

474
00:24:14,140 --> 00:24:15,380
I will arrange a time

475
00:24:15,560 --> 00:24:17,450
for you to apologize
to the Chairman in private.

476
00:24:17,450 --> 00:24:19,620
(Xiuya was very conflicted
at the moment.)

477
00:24:19,860 --> 00:24:21,780
(She felt that Zheng Hao and Shi Ye)

478
00:24:21,780 --> 00:24:23,060
(both made a good point.)
I'm leaving.

479
00:24:23,080 --> 00:24:24,420
(A whole day of excessive anxiety)

480
00:24:24,420 --> 00:24:25,900
(had made her lose her judgment.)

481
00:24:26,110 --> 00:24:28,150
(And the confrontation
between Zheng Hao and Shi Ye)

482
00:24:28,150 --> 00:24:29,620
(also reached a heated state.)

483
00:24:30,050 --> 00:24:31,160
(Xiuya wanted)

484
00:24:31,160 --> 00:24:32,930
(this debate that had started
because of her)

485
00:24:33,180 --> 00:24:34,220
(to end immediately.)

486
00:24:34,700 --> 00:24:35,540
Take it easy.

487
00:24:43,050 --> 00:24:44,090
Try this beer.

488
00:24:44,090 --> 00:24:45,420
It's freshly brewed here.

489
00:24:45,420 --> 00:24:47,420
It will spoil in seven days.

490
00:24:47,700 --> 00:24:49,940
Brother-in-law, I quit beer lately.

491
00:24:49,940 --> 00:24:51,090
I only drink red wine.

492
00:24:52,700 --> 00:24:53,900
Is it the high uric acid level?

493
00:24:54,460 --> 00:24:56,380
I'm at 780, you know?

494
00:24:56,700 --> 00:24:57,860
300 is the limit already.

495
00:24:57,860 --> 00:24:59,450
I have some good wine here.
I'll get it for you.

496
00:25:00,050 --> 00:25:00,900
Don't bother.

497
00:25:01,180 --> 00:25:02,900
Let's get down to the business.

498
00:25:02,900 --> 00:25:03,980
I have another appointment later.

499
00:25:04,380 --> 00:25:05,570
Alright, go ahead.

500
00:25:07,900 --> 00:25:09,330
We're all family here.

501
00:25:09,420 --> 00:25:10,900
I'll get straight to the point.

502
00:25:12,050 --> 00:25:14,570
I have some insider information.

503
00:25:15,180 --> 00:25:17,180
The development zone is about to change.

504
00:25:17,460 --> 00:25:19,700
I happen to have a friend
in real estate.

505
00:25:19,760 --> 00:25:21,090
He said he could
reserve a house for me.

506
00:25:21,700 --> 00:25:23,180
If I secure that house now,

507
00:25:23,220 --> 00:25:24,420
the price will go up in a few years.

508
00:25:25,180 --> 00:25:26,900
It's a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity.

509
00:25:28,140 --> 00:25:29,050
What I mean is,

510
00:25:29,860 --> 00:25:31,220
I lent you 250,000 yuan before

511
00:25:31,220 --> 00:25:32,330
to open the bar.

512
00:25:32,380 --> 00:25:34,220
It's been years now. Isn't it time
for you to pay back…?

513
00:25:38,330 --> 00:25:39,170
Wait.

514
00:25:39,460 --> 00:25:42,220
Did you just say you lent me 250,000?

515
00:25:43,090 --> 00:25:43,930
Yes.

516
00:25:44,180 --> 00:25:45,570
- To open the bar…
- Hold it.

517
00:25:45,570 --> 00:25:48,700
Back then, you said

518
00:25:48,700 --> 00:25:52,700
the money was an investment, right?

519
00:25:52,900 --> 00:25:53,740
What do you mean?

520
00:25:54,420 --> 00:25:55,900
What investment?

521
00:25:59,810 --> 00:26:00,650
Didn't you

522
00:26:01,620 --> 00:26:03,860
say that opening the bar

523
00:26:03,860 --> 00:26:05,110
was a good idea

524
00:26:05,110 --> 00:26:06,540
and it'd be profitable in the future?

525
00:26:06,540 --> 00:26:07,590
I said I wanted to borrow money,

526
00:26:07,590 --> 00:26:08,420
but you said unnecessary

527
00:26:08,420 --> 00:26:09,910
and you'd give me
the money as an investment.

528
00:26:09,910 --> 00:26:11,050
Wasn't that what you said?

529
00:26:11,940 --> 00:26:13,090
What? Now

530
00:26:13,590 --> 00:26:15,330
you see that this bar
isn't making money,

531
00:26:15,380 --> 00:26:16,570
so you call it a loan?

532
00:26:16,700 --> 00:26:18,220
I didn't ask you for a loan back then,

533
00:26:18,220 --> 00:26:20,180
but instead of a loan,

534
00:26:20,180 --> 00:26:21,700
you said it was an investment.

535
00:26:22,490 --> 00:26:25,180
For all these years, I have been
treating you as a shareholder.

536
00:26:25,180 --> 00:26:27,160
You never paid for drinks here.

537
00:26:27,160 --> 00:26:28,780
Isn't this the behavior
of a shareholder?

538
00:26:28,780 --> 00:26:30,140
What? Now the bar
is about to lose money,

539
00:26:30,140 --> 00:26:31,380
so you call it a loan?

540
00:26:31,380 --> 00:26:32,220
What do you mean?

541
00:26:32,380 --> 00:26:34,420
Brother-in-law, you're
going too far by saying that.

542
00:26:36,140 --> 00:26:38,140
When did I ever say
it was an investment?

